//Congential heart disease - Tetralogy of Fallot


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 of Cardio MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button
When I select 'Congential heart disease' tab
Then 'Congential heart disease' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Tetralogy of Fallot' from 'Congential heart disease' dropdown menu
Then 'Add pathology' button is enabled
And 'Ventricle septal defect (VSD)' checkbox is enabled
And 'RVOT obstruction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Right ventricular hypertrophy' checkbox is enabled
And 'Overriding aorta' checkbox is enabled
And 'Aortopulmonary collateral' checkbox is enabled
And 'Right-sided aortic arch' checkbox is enabled
And 'Coronary Artery Anomalies' checkbox is enabled
And 'Persistent left superior vena cava' checkbox is enabled
And 'Atrioventricular septal defect' checkbox is enabled


When I select 'Ventricle septal defect (VSD)' checkbox
Then 'Membranous' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'RVOT obstruction' checkbox
Then 'Infundibular pulmonary stenosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Pulmonary valve stenosis' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Coronary Artery Anomalies' checkbox
Then 'RIVA/LAD of the right coronary sinus' checkbox is enabled
When I select 'RIVA/LAD of the right coronary sinus' checkbox
Then 'Prepulmonary' checkbox is enabled
